y couldn=E2=80=99t effectively operate remotely and so finally moved to the=
 cloud over the last few years; the implication is that cloud growth is goi=
ng to be a lot slower going forward, just like PC sales or e-commerce. It=
=E2=80=99s a compelling argument, and would certainly explain why Microsoft=
 CEO Satya Nadella was so eager to talk about AI on the earnings call.

One other point on margins; AMD is back on top (its margin had dropped beca=
use of aggressive pricing on its consumers parts):

You would expect that, all things being equal, Intel would have better marg=
ins than AMD: after all, AMD has to share margin with TSMC. Interestingly e=
nough, though, the difference in margin this quarter comes down to Intel ma=
king its own chips: underutilization of its fabs cost the company four poin=
ts of margin, which is exactly how much better AMD=E2=80=99s margin was tha=
n Intel=E2=80=99s. It=E2=80=99s an excellent example of how high fixed-cost=
 businesses can be very profitable, but all too quickly go in the opposite =
direction.

